# WebTelemetry

Routes page-level telemetry signals to native clients. Settings gate individual signal types:

| Setting | Purpose |
|---------|---------|
| `webEvents` | Gate forwarding of webDetection events (required for eventHub pipeline) |
| `videoPlayback` | Gate video playback telemetry |
| `urlChanged` | Gate URL change telemetry |

Each setting uses `FeatureState` (`"enabled"` / `"disabled"`).

## webEvents and the detection pipeline

When `webEvents` is disabled, `fireWebEvent` calls from `webDetection` are silently dropped — no events reach `eventHub`. Enable `webEvents` in platform overrides to activate event messaging.
